The paper deals with the problem of sparse recovery, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The focus on minimizing the number of measurements and decoding time suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-fields of data structures (cs.DS) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the consideration of robustness and stability of the algorithm suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-field of signal processing (cs.SI).
